
<h3>OAuth 2 Ruby Sample</h3>
<div>1.Package the whole folder to your server, if you are running locally, your can use ngrok: https://ngrok.com/</div> </br>
<div>2.Update the config file located at Rails.root/config/config.yml with your Client ID, Client Secret, host uri and redirect_to URI</div> </br>
<div>3.Go to Developer.intuit.com, in your App, Add your Redirect_uri</div> </br>
<div>Note: the logic is located at app/controllers/token_controller.rb</div>

<h1>Below are the current QBO Account Attributes:</h1>
<p>
  Access Token: <%= @qbo_account.access_token %><br>
  Refresh Token: <%= @qbo_account.refresh_token %><br>
  QBO Account Created At: <%= @qbo_account.created_at %><br>
  QBO Account Updated At: <%= @qbo_account.updated_at %><br>
</p>

<% if @qbo_account.persisted? %>
  <%= link_to('Refresh Your OAuth Token', edit_token_path(@qbo_account)) %> <br>
  <%= button_to('Delete Your OAuth Token', token_path(@qbo_account), method: :delete) %> <br>
<% end %>

<div>Click the Below button to start the flow:</div><br>
<%= link_to(image_tag("/C2QB_white_btn_med_default.png"), params[:url]) %>
<br><br>
<div>Remember to update your Redirect URIs in your app:</div>
<%= link_to(image_tag("/app_redirect.png")) %>
